# ============================================================

# .gitignore — Enterprise Security Assessment Lab

# Purpose: Prevent accidental credential, token, hash, cloud key,

# VM image, raw tool-output, and sensitive lab-data leaks.

#

# Important:

# - Screenshot evidence is allowed.

# - Raw secrets, hashes, tokens, Terraform state, cloud credentials,

# packet captures, VM images, and private keys are blocked.

# - Review every commit before pushing:

# git status

# git diff --cached

# ============================================================

# ============================================================

# 🔐 1. Environment Files and General Secrets

# ============================================================

.env
.env.*
*.env
secrets.txt
secret.txt
credentials.txt
credential.txt
creds.txt
passwords.txt
password.txt
passwd.txt
tokens.txt
token.txt
api_keys.txt
apikeys.txt
api-key.txt
private-notes.txt
sensitive.txt

# ============================================================

# ☁️ 2. AWS / Azure / GCP Cloud Credentials

# ============================================================

# AWS

.aws/
aws_credentials*
aws-credentials*
cloudgoat-start.txt
start.txt
cloudgoat_start.txt
cloudgoat-credentials.txt
cloudgoat_credentials.txt

# Azure

.azure/
azureProfile.json
accessTokens.json

# GCP

.gcloud/
application_default_credentials.json
adc.json

# Cloud CLI cached credentials

*_credentials.json
*_credential.json
service-account-key.json
service_account_key.json

